    <div class="profile_content">
      <h3>Joel Portice - President, Verisk Health, Payment Integrity Division.</h3>
      <p>
        Since 2009, Joel has been President and CEO of Intelimedix, a healthcare data analytics and software company. Previously, Joel served as COO at HCI, where he developed and executed the growth strategy, including product management, financial performance and product enhancements and direction while also leading overall operations with profit and loss oversight.
Before joining HCI, he cofounded Enclarity, Inc., a healthcare information management and analytics solutions company. Prior to launching Enclarity, he was VP of Healthcare and Insurance Analytics for Fair Isaac Corporation. Joel also cofounded Integrity Plus Services, a cost-containment software and services company that served the healthcare and insurance markets.  IPS was acquired by UnitedHealth Group and became part of its Ingenix subsidiary.
Joel received his bachelor of science degree from the University of South Dakota and a master of arts degree from Hamline University. He is a member of the board of trustees for Hamline University and the board of advisors for the Center for Health Care Management and Policy of the Paul Merage School of Business at the University of California, Irvine.
      </p>
